{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://wwfalcon.github.io/sdc_toolkits_page/","title":"PSD SDC Toolkits","description":"PSD SDC Toolkits."}},"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"","date":null,"date_pretty":null,"path":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"image":null,"next":null,"sidebar":null,"toc":null,"keywords":null},"html":"<h1 id=\"识别目标客户群以关注你的营销资源\"><a href=\"#%E8%AF%86%E5%88%AB%E7%9B%AE%E6%A0%87%E5%AE%A2%E6%88%B7%E7%BE%A4%E4%BB%A5%E5%85%B3%E6%B3%A8%E4%BD%A0%E7%9A%84%E8%90%A5%E9%94%80%E8%B5%84%E6%BA%90\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>识别目标客户群以关注你的营销资源</h1>\n<p><strong>创建目标客户群（称为细分</strong> 是根据市场子群之间的相似性划分产品市场的过程。细分的目的是帮助公司识别其最具吸引力的细分市场，以便可以将营销资源集中在这些客户上。</p>\n<h2 id=\"如何细分市场\"><a href=\"#%E5%A6%82%E4%BD%95%E7%BB%86%E5%88%86%E5%B8%82%E5%9C%BA\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>如何细分市场</h2>\n<p>细分涉及开发和评级应用场景，以识别特定市场中最具吸引力的客户群。以下流程说明了该过程。详细说明如下。</p>\n<h2 id=\"步骤1：创建目标细分列表\"><a href=\"#%E6%AD%A5%E9%AA%A41%EF%BC%9A%E5%88%9B%E5%BB%BA%E7%9B%AE%E6%A0%87%E7%BB%86%E5%88%86%E5%88%97%E8%A1%A8\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>步骤1：创建目标细分列表</h2>\n<p>创建以用户为中心的场景，以创建潜在利基目标细分的完整列表。 （你可能希望阅读关于<a href=\"/sdc_toolkits_page/concepts/identifying-target-customers-for-a-social-enterprise_zh_CN\">目标客户</a>的单独文章）。</p>\n<h2 id=\"步骤2：将搜索范围缩小到最有希望的目标细分市场\"><a href=\"#%E6%AD%A5%E9%AA%A42%EF%BC%9A%E5%B0%86%E6%90%9C%E7%B4%A2%E8%8C%83%E5%9B%B4%E7%BC%A9%E5%B0%8F%E5%88%B0%E6%9C%80%E6%9C%89%E5%B8%8C%E6%9C%9B%E7%9A%84%E7%9B%AE%E6%A0%87%E7%BB%86%E5%88%86%E5%B8%82%E5%9C%BA\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>步骤2：将搜索范围缩小到最有希望的目标细分市场</h2>\n<p>根据“跨越鸿沟/保龄球道标准”对场景进行排名（有关详细信息，请参阅<a href=\"/sdc_toolkits_page/concepts/technology-adoption-lifecycle-talc_zh_CN\">技术采用生命周期[TALC]</a>）：</p>\n<ul>\n<li>是否可以获得经济买家，并且他们资金充足？</li>\n<li>经济买家是否有非常令人信服的理由购买（CRTB - Compelling Reason To Buy）？</li>\n<li>是否提供可行的整体产品解决方案？</li>\n<li>会面临缺乏既定竞争吗？</li>\n<li>是否有积极的后续潜力？</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong><em>注意：重复步骤1和2，直到找到一个独立的目标细分市场。</em></strong></p>\n<h2 id=\"步骤3：选择具有最大潜力的目标客户\"><a href=\"#%E6%AD%A5%E9%AA%A43%EF%BC%9A%E9%80%89%E6%8B%A9%E5%85%B7%E6%9C%89%E6%9C%80%E5%A4%A7%E6%BD%9C%E5%8A%9B%E7%9A%84%E7%9B%AE%E6%A0%87%E5%AE%A2%E6%88%B7\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>步骤3：选择具有最大潜力的目标客户</h2>\n<p>客户应根据自身优势发挥吸引力，并在制定<a href=\"/sdc_toolkits_page/concepts/product-strategy-in-product-development-and-the-whole-product_zh_CN\">产品战略</a>和客户参考的基础上提供最佳的后续市场潜力。每个客户代表潜在的细分市场。使用<a href=\"/sdc_toolkits_page/concepts/the-mdsc-market-development-strategy-checklist-providing-strategic-direction-for-startups-go-to-market-programs_zh_CN\">市场开发战略清单</a>制定计划以赢得领先细分市场。</p>\n<h2 id=\"步骤4：使用市场研究验证当前的思考和假设\"><a href=\"#%E6%AD%A5%E9%AA%A44%EF%BC%9A%E4%BD%BF%E7%94%A8%E5%B8%82%E5%9C%BA%E7%A0%94%E7%A9%B6%E9%AA%8C%E8%AF%81%E5%BD%93%E5%89%8D%E7%9A%84%E6%80%9D%E8%80%83%E5%92%8C%E5%81%87%E8%AE%BE\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>步骤4：使用<a href=\"/sdc_toolkits_page/concepts/market-research-for-startups-find-your-target-market-customers-and-competition_zh_CN\">市场研究</a>验证当前的思考和假设</h2>\n<p>你可以选择在市场规划之前进行研究，或者在产品进入市场的同时进行研究。通过测试你的策略，你可以在启动新的市场开发计划之前测试你所做的假设。</p>\n<h2 id=\"参考资料\"><a href=\"#%E5%8F%82%E8%80%83%E8%B5%84%E6%96%99\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>参考资料</h2>\n<p>Wiefels, P. (2002). <em>The Chasm Companion</em>. New York: Harper Business.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/concepts/identifying-target-customer-segments-to-focus-your-marketing-resources_zh_CN/"},"timeToRead":3,"excerpt":"…","fileAbsolutePath":"/Users/gavinwang/Documents/Working/codes/sdc_toolkits/content/concepts/identifying-target-customer-segments-to-focus-your-marketing-resources_zh_CN.md"}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/concepts/identifying-target-customer-segments-to-focus-your-marketing-resources_zh_CN/"}}